The paper deals with finding a distribution for an associated entropic vector, which involves concepts from information theory (IT) such as entropy and probability mass function. The algorithmic approach and numerical solutions suggest a focus on computer science (CS) sub-categories such as data structures (DS), discrete mathematics (DM), and computational complexity (CC). The paper also discusses applications and comparisons with known results, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (SI).
